==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek (''empyrios''), from (''em'') + (''pur''), which means "fire."

===Adjective===
'''empyreal'''
# Pertaining to the highest heaven or the [[empyrean]]; celestial; sublime; exalted.
# Of the sky or heavens.
# Fiery, made of pure fire.

